<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Time Stamp Microservice</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-BVYiiSIFeK1dGmJRAkycuHAHRg32OmUcww7on3RYdg4Va+PmSTsz/K68vbdEjh4u"crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Unix Time Stamp Converter</h1>
    <br/>
    
    <div>
      <p><b>Today's Date: </b><%=todayDate%></p>
      <p><b>Current Time Stamp:</b> <%=todayTimeStamp%></p>
    </div>
    
    
    
    
    <div class="container">
      <div class="jumbotron">
      <p> <h3><b>Instructions</b></h3></p>
      <div>
        <ol>
        <li>In order to obtain Unix Time stamp from an alphabetic date, append your year, month and day into url using the following format <br><br>
        <u>url/date?year=1991&month=01&day=28</u></li><br>
        
        <li>If you have a Unix Timestamp you want to convert to alphabetic date simply append your timestamp the following way
        (note, input timestamp in milliseconds)<br><br>
        <u>url/timestamp</u> </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
